definitions.definition: Any of the headings under which each of the main divisions of a subject may be subdivided.
A heading or caption subordinate to a main headline, heading, or title especially when inserted as a divider between sections (as of a newspaper or periodical article or story or text of a book).

main_definition: Any of the headings under which each of the main divisions of a subject may be subdivided.
